Arsenal manager Arsene Wenger has revealed his World Cup winning trio will almost certainly miss the Premier League opener against Crystal Palace.

Mesut Ozil, Per Mertesacker and Lukas Podolski are on a well-deserved break after helping Germany to success in Brazil.

The threesome will not return to pre-season training until August 11, just five days prior to the clash against Tony Pulis' side.

