Despite the commercial gain, Van Gaal claims long distance summer tours are not beneficial for the development of his team.

And Wenger added: 'Sometimes our training camps are decided for commercial reasons to extend the popularity of the club.

'We
 have been to Asia, of course, and we have many fans there. This is the 
first time for us to come to the States and I'm very happy we can come 
to New York because its a city I love.

'But
 for purely football reasons the best for football is not to travel too 
much because of the time you have to wait and the jet lag is not ideal.'

